<p style="text-align: justify">&nbsp;</p>
<h2 style="text-align: justify;font-weight: normal">BRKB shares: paying dividends</h2>
<p>Fashions on the stock market come and go, and while technology is the current fad, it should be remembered that the Berkshire Hathaway share price has been based on long held dividend plays, not quick position flipping.</p>
<p>For instance, Warren Buffett’s entry on Coca Cola shares was so low and so long ago, BRKB shares received a yield of 50% on the holding. This is a performance that few companies can either match or sustain.</p>
